<TEXT>
<P>
 LONG ROAD TO FREEDOM: The Advocate History of the Gay and Lesbian Movement 
edited by Mark Thompson, foreword by Randy Shilts. (St. Martin's: $40; 420 pp.) 
Here is a history of the modern gay and lesbian movement, with essays, 
photographs, cartoons and interviews from the Advocate, that siren of gay life 
since 1967. There's a lot of humor and a lot of chagrin, but best of all, it 
feels like a family photo album. 
</P>
