<TEXT>
<P>
 UNDERSTANDING COMICS: The Invisible Art by Scott McCloud (HarperPerennial: 
$20; 216 pp.) . Despite their enormous popularity all over the world, comic 
strips and comic books have been the subject of remarkably little serious 
critical analysis. McCloud offer an unusually intelligent overview of the 
popular art form built on sequential visual images, usually juxtaposed with 
dialogue and/or verbal descriptions. Noting that this powerful medium has 
seldom been used for more than superficial entertainment in America, he 
stresses that its potential remains largely untapped. Readers may find 
themselves looking at familiar newspaper strips with new respect. 
</P>
