<HEADLINE>
<P>
STYLE: FASHION; STRETCHING IT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROCHELLE SPEARMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Neon colors and dizzying prints are fine for high-energy aerobics, but yoga 
calls for workout clothes more in keeping with the exercise's slow, deliberate 
stretching and meditative breathing.The latest looks include palettes and 
patterns that reflect nature's serenity: soft watercolors and pretty florals 
for women, simple charcoal and other solid neutrals for men. Cotton and Lycra 
are more absorbent and "breathable" than before, making clothes both stylishly 
snug and comfortable. Yoga contributes to a sense of quiet well-being; now what 
you wear can, too. ROCHELLE SPEARMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
