<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP MUSIC CHARTS: IMPRESSIVE NUMBERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Teen-aged R&B singer Aaliyah is a protege of R. Kelly, who's noted for his 
racy material . Though he wrote, produced and raps on her single, "Back and 
Forth," it's not that racy--but it's a big hit: No. 4 on The Times' Southern 
California pop singles chart. Her first album, "Age Ain't Nothing But a 
Number," is doing well too: No. 17 on the pop chart. Unlike some rap artists 
who make splashy chart debuts and then fade, Warren G. is apparently no 
flash-in-the-pan. His "Regulate" album still tops the pop, rap and R&B charts. 
