<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AND ONE MORE THING: Baby, you can drive Ringo's car. The former Beatles 
drummer's '57 Chevy is the centerpiece item of a rock memorabilia auction being 
conducted by a firm called It's Only Rock 'n' Roll of Huntington Station, N.Y. 
The company expects the vehicle -- said to be in mint condition -- to fetch 
more than $30,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The unique thing about this auction, though, is you don't have to be there to 
check out the merchandise. The company is billing it as the "first ever video 
rock 'n' roll auction" -- all the items can be "previewed" on a videotape made 
by the firm, and bids will be taken by mail, phone and fax, with items being 
sold Tuesday and Wednesday evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
