<P>
4 MIAMI POLICEMEN CONVICTED OF COVERUP IN DEALER'S DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four police officers were convicted of misleading investigators to cover up a 
1988 beating death of a drug dealer. 
</P>
<P>
 Pablo Camacho, Charlie Haynes Jr., Nathaniel Veal Jr. and Andy Watson were 
found guilty last week of one count of multiple charges of obstruction of 
justice and misleading law enforcement officers. Each faces a maximum 10 years 
in prison. 
</P>
<P>
 In 1990, the four officers were acquitted of charges they conspired to violate 
Leonardo Mercado's civil rights by killing him. The verdicts sparked rioting in 
Wynwood, the Puerto Rican neighborhood where Mercado lived. 
</P>
