<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE HONOR IS MORE THAN PUBLIC RELATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Thank you for the story on the Police Appreciation Day sponsored by the 
Kiwanis Clubs of Glendale. However, the salute is intended for all the officers 
of the Glendale Police Department.If the clubs were to "recognize the good 
officers," each and every one would have to be recognized. 
</P>
<P>
 This day is set aside to honor those police officers who have risked their own 
lives to protect or save the life of another person or for heroism above and 
beyond the call of duty. 
</P>
<P>
 Since the program was started in 1988 by the Gateway Kiwanis Club of Glendale, 
it had nothing to do with "combatting negative publicity stemming from the 
Rodney King beating trials" as you wrote. 
</P>
