<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHEAST: SOUTH GATE; SUSPECT IS SOUGHT IN TRANSIENT'S DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police and Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies were still looking for the 
man who killed Leonardo Padilla, a 35-year-old transient who was badly beaten 
June 4 and died three days later at King-Drew Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Paramedics had found Padilla near the 4400 block of Firestone Boulevard, lying 
on the ground with head injuries. The coroner's report said that Padilla died 
of a blow to the head, Sheriff's Sgt. Ron Spear said. 
</P>
<P>
 South Gate police have located witnesses who said they saw two men fighting 
that night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
