COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: PIRU; 3-YEAR-OLD BOY BITTEN BY RATTLER, HOSPITALIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 3-year-old Piru boy was in good and stable condition Saturday after being 
bitten on the foot by a rattlesnake in the driveway of his home. 
</P>
<P>
 Salvador Ciseners was in the intensive care unit at Santa Paula Memorial 
Hospital, a nursing supervisor said. 
</P>
<P>
 Shortly after 9 p.m. Friday, the toddler tried to pick up a foot-long rattler 
that was stretched out in the driveway of his family's home on Main Street in 
Piru. The snake bit him on the inside of his left foot, Ventura County fire 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 "I guess he thought it was a lizard," Capt. Elliot Handy said. "He picked up 
this rattlesnake and it bit him in the foot. It was fairly serious." The leg 
swelled considerably, Handy said, before the boy was transported to the 
hospital. Firefighters killed the small snake. TRACY WILSON 
