</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Folha de Sao Paulo 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 To say that Brazilians are not enamored of Colombians is an 
understatement.This, from Jose Simao, a columnist in Sao Paulo: 
</P>
<P>
 "The Colombian fans? They're hilarious. Everyone's got a yellow wig like 
(Colombian midfielder Carlos) Valderrama, everyone's got a face like bozo. I 
went down the final minutes of the game (against the United States) to the 
hotel bar. Two televisions were on. The gringos were applauding. I thought, 
'They're applauding the victory over Colombia.' Nope. They were applauding the 
basketball game that was on the television behind me." 
