<HEADLINE>
<P>
AMERICAN LEGION BASEBALL ; WESTLAKE-ROYAL TO PLAY FOR TITLE AFTER DEFEATING 
VALLEY RANGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brian Schuster's eighth-inning single drove in the winning run for the 
Westlake-Royal American Legion team in a 7-6 victory against the Valley Rangers 
in a semifinal of the Sierra Nevada Classic Saturday at Reno. 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake-Royal (13-2-1) will face either San Mateo or Reno in the championship 
game today at 3 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Schuster's hit was set up when Joel Mellinger led off the eighth with a single 
and took third on Randy Wolf's wild pickoff throw. The Valley Rangers, a 
Glendale-based Connie Mack team that includes some of the San Fernando Valley's 
best players, intentionally walked the next two batters to bring up Schuster. 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake-Royal sent the game into extra innings with two runs in the bottom of 
the seventh, scoring the tying run on a two-out wild pitch. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodland Hills East 12, Burbank South 1 -- Rusty Jenkins struck out nine and 
scattered three hits over seven innings as Woodland Hills East won a game 
called after seven innings at Taft High. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott Horowitz and Greg Venger each drove in two runs for Woodland Hills East 
(2-7). Burbank South scored an unearned run in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodland Hills West 16, Antelope Valley South 4 -- John Novak had five hits 
and Justin Balser added four, leading Woodland Hills West in a District 20 game 
at Antelope Valley High. Craig Carlton pitched a complete game, giving up only 
one earned run. The game was called after seven innings because of the 10-run 
rule. 
</P>
<P>
 Canoga Park 10, Van Nuys East 4 -- Gus Lomeli pitched a complete game for his 
third consecutive victory as Canoga Park won for the sixth time in seven games. 
David Vargas had two hits and two RBIs for Canoga Park (7-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Granada Hills East 10, Mission Hills 9 -- Granada Hills scored seven runs in 
the ninth inning to pull out a District 20 victory at Alemany. Aldo Pinto 
scored the winning run on a sacrifice fly by George Kassis. 
</P>
<P>
 Newhall-Santa Clarita 19, Burbank North 0 -- Lucas Solomon pitched four 
scoreless innings and was three for three with two doubles, leading 
Newhall-Santa Clarita (9-1) in a District 20 game at Burbank High. 
</P>
<P>
 West Hills 6, Palmdale 4 -- Adam Crecion homered and pitched five scoreless 
innings, picking up the victory for West Hills (5-5) in a District 20 game at 
Chaminade High. 
</P>
