LOCAL NOTES; PIETROWSKI EASILY ADVANCES TO SECTIONAL TENNIS FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jakub Pietrowski of Huntington Beach, top-seeded in the boys' 18 main draw, 
defeated fourth-seeded Nate Jackmon of Goleta, 6-1, 6-3, Saturday to advance to 
the final of the Southern California Junior Sectionals today at Los Caballeros 
Sports Village in Fountain Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Top-seeded Joseph Gilbert and fifth-seeded Ryan Moore, both from Fullerton, 
will meet in the boys' 16 final at 10:30 a.m. today.Gilbert advanced with a 
6-4, 6-3 semifinal victory over Canoga Park's Dylan Mann. Moore defeated Palm 
Springs' Andrew Scorteanu, 6-1, 7-5, in the other semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
 Faye Devera, third-seeded in the girls' 16 main draw, lost to top-seeded 
Alexandra Stevenson of San Diego, 6-3, 6-3, in a semifinal match. Stevenson 
will play Mugette Ahn of Los Angeles in today's final at noon. 
</P>
<P>
 Pietrowski will face second-seeded Derek Pope from Ojai at noon for the boys' 
18 title. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The second "All-Star Basketball Challenge," featuring top players from Orange 
County against standouts from San Diego County, will be held at 7 tonight at 
Del Mar Torrey Pines High School. 
</P>
<P>
 The Orange County all-star team is led by 6-foot-6 forward Tony Gonzalez from 
Huntington Beach. Among his teammates are Century's Thomas Harmon, Pacifica's 
Chris Vlasic, Orange's Gil Gonzales, University's Demetrius Zeigler and Santa 
Margarita twins Brad and Brian Finneran. 
</P>
<P>
 The team is coached by Santa Ana Valley assistant coach Paul Hoover. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, San Diego won, 107-89. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $5 for adults and $3 for children 12 and younger. There will be a 
three-point shootout at halftime, and a slam-dunk competition after the game. 
</P>
