<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; HAWAII READIES FOR 'CUISINES OF THE SUN' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There's a chili in the air on the Big Island of Hawaii where organizers are 
getting ready for the fifth annual "Cuisines of the Sun" festival, featuring 
the food of "Chili Climates." 
</P>
<P>
 The three-day festival opens July 23 at the Mauna Lani Bay Hotel and 
Bungalows.Guest chefs will include Rick Bayless, author of the book "Authentic 
Mexico"; Julie Sahni, author of "Classic Indian Cooking" and Emeril Lagasse, 
chef of Emeril's and NOLA in New Orleans. 
</P>
<P>
 A "Cuisines of the Sun" package, including four nights in an ocean-view 
accommodation and attendance at all 10 Cuisines events, is available for $1,480 
single occupancy, $2,180 double. The cuisine program is offered independently 
at $700 and nightly room rates are $225. For reservations, call (800) 367-2323. 
Getting to the Hong Kong Airport 
</P>
<P>
 New, slightly higher fares have been announced for Hong Kong's airport bus 
services. A ticket to the Tsimshatsui tourist district in Kowloon is now about 
$1.40. Service between the airport and the Macao Ferry Terminal, Causeway Bay 
and the Tai Koo Shing are all $2.05. The buses, which use circular routes and 
stop near many of the city's major hotels, are a bargain: A taxi into Hong Kong 
will set you back $9. 
</P>
</TEXT>
