<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; JUST THE FACTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 THE CLEANEST AND DIRTIEST CITIES IN EUROPE 
</P>
<P>
 London is Europe's cleanest city and Athens the dirtiest, according Tidy 
Britain Group, an anti-litter organization.The biannual study surveyed areas in 
nine European capitals for litter, graffiti and other unsightliness. Tidy 
Britain's rankings and comments: 
</P>
<P>
 London -- The highest number of Grade A sites -- no litter. Berne -- Generally 
very clean. Paris -- The dirtiest shopping street. Berlin -- Enormous 
infrastructure and development pressure. Many survey streets were inaccessible. 
Amsterdam -- The graffiti capital Brussels -- Slipped from fourth place since 
1991. Rome -- The Romans have not yet learned to poop-scoop. Madrid -- The 
dog-fouling capital of Europe Athens -- A virtual plague of cigarette ends. 
</P>
