<HEADLINE>
<P>
BACKPACK & BUDGET; CANADIAN ROCKIES IN FIVE BUS STOPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LUCY IZON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After last year's successful summer, the Rocky Express budget bus service will 
once again take travelers on do-as-you-please weekly tours of the Canadian 
Rockies. 
</P>
<P>
 True North Tours, in association with Hostelling Alberta, is offering 
five-night programs that depart each Sunday through October. 
</P>
<P>
 A 15-seat passenger van picks up a maximum of 14 people from the Calgary and 
Banff hostels and transports them to a variety of activities in a different 
area of the Rockies each day. Stops include Lake Louise, the Columbia 
Icefields, Athabasca Falls and Jasper. 
</P>
<P>
 Activities range from hiking, canoeing, touring a glacier in an all-terrain 
vehicle, horseback riding, white-water rafting and biking. 
</P>
<P>
 Each evening the bus delivers passengers to a different hostel where beds have 
been reserved. Hostels range in price from $5.50 to $11 per night for dormitory 
accommodations. 
</P>
<P>
 The price for the transportation is $94.50. Passengers must provide their own 
meals. All of the hostels have their own kitchens, and in some locations it is 
possible to dine out. 
</P>
<P>
 This tour is available to anyone, any age, whether they are members of an 
affiliated hostel association or not. 
</P>
<P>
 For further information, contact Banff International Hostel, P.O. Box 1358, 
Tunnel Mountain Road, Banff, Alberta T0L 0C0; telephone (800) 363-0096. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Travelers using VIA Rail's unlimited travel Canrailpasses this year (including 
those buying the reduced youth or senior versions) will be getting an extra 
perk, a Hello Phone Pass (value $14) valid for complimentary long-distance 
calls. 
</P>
<P>
 The Canrailpass is valid for 12 days of coach-class rail travel within a 
30-day period, anywhere in Canada that VIA services. The regular price of a 
high season pass (June 1 to Sept. 30) is $357, travelers age 2 to 24 pay $322. 
The regular price during low season (Oct. 1 to Dec. 14) is $244, youths pay 
$223. 
</P>
<P>
 Pass holders are required to obtain tickets before boarding, and because the 
number of seats available to pass holders is limited, it is recommended that 
tickets be obtained early. 
</P>
<P>
 Pass holders are also offered discounts at Choice Hotels and a version of the 
Canrailpass, which includes three days of car rental. 
</P>
<P>
 Travelers age 12 to 24 who buy tickets for VIA coach, first class or sleeping 
accommodation services are also eligible for a 10% discount throughout the 
system. For details see your travel agent. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 A former hotel in Fort Lauderdale has joined the American Youth Hostels 
network and is now offering low-cost dormitory accommodation, scuba lessons and 
trips to the Everglades. 
</P>
<P>
 The HI-Fort Lauderdale International House is across from the beach at 3811 N. 
Ocean Blvd., Fort Lauderdale, Fla. 33308. 
</P>
<P>
 It can accommodate 96 travelers in air-conditioned rooms with four and eight 
beds. The overnight fee is $12 for members of Hostelling International and $15 
for non-members. 
</P>
<P>
 There are kitchen facilities, a garden/barbecue area and a swimming pool. 
Trips to the Everglades are arranged in the hostel van for $15. 
</P>
<P>
 Economical snorkeling, reef diving, underwater sightseeing and wreck-diving 
excursions can all be arranged for hostel guests. A scuba certification course 
for theory and practical instruction in the swimming pool and the ocean, costs 
$135. Fees include the use of equipment, instruction and air refills.  
</P>
<P>
 Call the hostel for reservations at (305) 568-1615. 
</P>
</TEXT>
